Package: polean
Type: Package
Title: Complex-Encoded Semi-Boolean Extension of the R Logical Type
Version: 0.9.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Philip", family = "Eigen", email = "pceigen@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0001-5000-7396"))
Description: Provides a non-propagating extension of R's logical type. In addition to TRUE, FALSE, and NA, polean introduces ISH(1) and ISH(0): values that share numerical equivalence with TRUE and FALSE but not boolean equivalence. Each value is represented internally as a complex number whose real part carries the truth orientation and whose imaginary part records whether the value is strict or ish. Coercion behavior is defined to avoid the propagation that NA would force.
